{
  "stem": "27687.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had somehow a fund for people who didn't work, who had no-- no resources, and so we lived on that.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And 1936, we went also to a separate school.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so we had the Jewish school, and we had all the professors from the university and the doctors, and they all were teaching us.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so actually we had a very good education.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But for me, it didn't help me much, because you were living under so much fear.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because 1938 there was the Kristallnacht and-- and then I didn't know if I would go to the camp or we couldn't leave Germany.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so in 1940, it probably was about August or September 1940, they came to our house early in the morning, and they said you have 15 minutes to take baggage of approximately 50-- 50 pound per person, and you have to go to the K school for assembly.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The arm-- the SR.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The German party from the Nazi party.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so I packed up 50 pounds--",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, I took some books.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I took the Bible with me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I took books mostly.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I had, oh, history books from-- and then I had some-- I had a little-- made a little radio what I made myself, but it never worked after that, because you got to-- you had to be in the big city so that the little crystal radio would work.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I took that anyhow with me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we took some clothes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And, well, that was it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we went down there, and they came with buses.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They loaded us up in buses and, well, but the funny part was that these boys what lived around me, they came and helped us to carry the baggage.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
